        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 10:30PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1028 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Grass Range, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grass Range, along with portions of Highway 89 from south of Grass
Range to the Fergus and Musselshell county lines.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
